<br>
At 39-40:  Set up camp at the first &quot;bend&quot; in the cave.  The cave consists of several hallways with turns all greater than 90 degrees.  The tricky part is finding a good spot and pulling to it.  This is made trickier by the fact that the Yetis and your pet will walk through the walls of the cave.  If the pet goes into a wall, immediately tell him to follow you, or, after the fight, you could lose him forever.  To pull, go into the cave, spot a yeti, then double back around the most recent bend.  From there, cast your favorite nuke or Malise if you like (I didn't really need it much).  Then run like hell back to the other end of the hallway from your pet.  Start nuking like heck.  When he finally gets on you, run toward your pet, keep running back and forth along the hallway until the pet strips it off.  &lt;insert favorite kill tactics here&gt;<br>
<br>
41-42:  Sit in the first bend outside the room at the end of the yeti tunnel.  Pull directly out of the room, but do NOT fight in the room.  You can pull singles with spells, but as soon as your pet gets into that room, they will all jump on him.  I'd fight in the &quot;second&quot; hallway out of the room (exit room, leave pet at first bend, use the hallway past that as your strip/nuke zone)<br>
<br>
43-44?<br>
If your int is above 175 or so, sit in the room.  You'll have to do a little bit of tanking here to conserve mana, but it IS possible to solo all 5 spawns.  Here's a little tip - some Yeti's will appear and wander out.  If something appears, unless you know another one will spawn soon, you can just let it be.  It may (especially in the &quot;front&quot; 3 spwans) wander out.  If it does, it will be back in 4 minutes or so, plenty of time to med up, and even off one of his bretheren.  I'm not sure what XP is like here, but I'd continue using the 39 earth pet, unless you're a lucky &amp;*@#%$&amp; and already have 44 earth.  At 44, you can move to one of the other caves, but be careful!!<br>
<br>
A WARNING:  Occasionally (happend thrice in 5 days for me), something else will spawn in the back room.  Don't attack it!! It is tougher than the yetis there.  Let me repeat, DO NOT ATTACK IT!!!!  It will naturally wander out to it's own area.  To prevent being jumped by these extras, and the Yetis when they spawn, I'd reccomend you sit to the right of the door, about 70 degrees around the room.<br>
<br>
Good luck to you... and if you fail, try again.  This place got me from 40 to 44 in 5 days. <p><a href="mailto:naginata@magecompendium.com">Naginata Kuroshio, Master of the Elements</a><BR>
Magician of the 44th Circle<BR>
Phoenix Reborn<BR>
