<br>
For starters.  What I used.  Focused 40 dmg hitting Fire pet with 2 Rune Swords.  Malise.  Blaze.  Renew Summoning.  Gate.  And make sure to always keep your buffs up as your going to get hit a few times even if your careful.  Nothing to worry about though.<br>
<br>
If you pull with spells you don't seem to aggro any extras.  The Yetis have a extremely small aggro range, so you should just make sure the way behind you is clear and then pull with Malise.  Now, just let your pet build up a few seconds of taunt and then chain nuke two Blazes into the yeti.  If they both hit for full or near full damage the yeti should turn to run.  Just make sure it doesn't run into any other Yetis and you'll be fine.<br>
<br>
BAMM.!!!  You just made some of the easiest experience your going to find at this level.  Now med up that bubble or two that you just used while your pet waits patiently for you to catch up.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Now just start spacing out the spawns a few minutes or more apart between your kills using the same tatics.<br>
<br>
Using these tatics I was able to take and control the room that is straight in.  Just make sure not to use more than 2 Nukes unless you must.  Otherwise you risk the possibility of a wanderer popping and not being able to take him.  If your nukes hit for quite a bit but it looks like your pet might die, just give him a heal and step in for a few hits.<br>
<br>
Easiest experience I've gotten since I did the Golras in Timorous Deep.  I went from a pixel into 39th to 40th in about 5 hours.  This was sharing the cave over with a druid though, so if you had both caves you could possibly go quicker. <p><a href=mailto:Zaknafinis@Hotmail.com>Zaknafinis Convoquer (Shining Alliance)</a><BR>Magician of the 40th level<BR>Prexus</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unanamarinfernostorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nanamar Infernostorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(9/25/00 3:07:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels3943.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Yetis.  Yetis, Yetis, Yetis</span><hr size=1> I'm soloing in overthere with about 1/2 min downtime, and only nuking a cinderbolt to pull, is it wise to switch to yetis?  I'm about to turn 40 in like 8 more kills, thats like 20 minutes of straight fights... <p><body text=50/100/10> <hr><b>Nanamar Infernostorm</b><br>
