<br>
1. You do not necessarity have to pull right back into the tunnel.  Stand just inside the tunnel and cast.  As the yeti reaches the tunnel entrance send in the pet.  You can actually send the pet into the cave to attack the yeti but if the victim starts to wander a second may join in.<br>
2. Keep phantom chain up.<br>
3. Malise is a waste of mana since there is rarely a resist to blaze or shock-of-swords.<br>
4. If you can kill the yetis in the cave, you can kill the wanderer.  It may be a bit tougher but not by much (sometimes the statics are also tougher than usual).<br>
5. Since the megapatch there seem to be more wanderers.  My only death in the cave was when I was attacked by 2 wanderers as I was killing the single spawn static.<br>
6. If you only burn once, pet will get half the exp.  You need at least 2x blaze + 1x shock to get full mana.  It is your call whether you want to med more for the extra exp.<br>
7.  If you can get 2 mages together, this place rocks.  Slaughter everything inside then go outside for a couple of drolvargs/drachnids/giants/chickens/wandering yetis while you wait for the cave to repopulate.<br>
8. Don't throw away the flowers.  They are worth 1pp+ at vendors (I've found no other use for them).<br>
<br>
Good hunting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubouya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bouya</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(12/11/00 2:58:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels3943.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://bouya.nexen.net/membres/tibouya.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tundra yeti cave</span><hr size=1> I made 38 to 44 in the n°1 cave in dreadlands, some yetis are greens at 43, and more at 44.<br>
