<br>
I thought I would relay my experiences in the Yeti caves.  First off, I spent most of my time in Cave #1 as denoted above.  There was only one time where that cave was camped and I moved to cave #9.  Cave #7 was off limits because the glacier yetis were too hard to kill.<br>
<br>
Cave 1<br>
<br>
There are a total of 7 static spawns with a single spawn at the crossroads and 3 spawns in the two rooms at the end of the caves.  The spawn time for the static spawns is 20 mins.  <br>
<br>
There is also a wandering spawn which will pop in either of two different spots: at the crossroads or at the mouth of one of the rooms.  Depending on which wanderer spawns, the mob path is a little different. One pop will wander into one room and the other pop will wander into the other.  Regardless, the wanderer will go past the crossroads and walk into the wall.  The spawn time for the wanderer is 16 mins.<br>
<br>
When I come to the caves initially, I would kill the wanderer and then start the stop watch.  I would then proceed to kill the crossroads mob, and then setup in the hallway near one of the rooms.  I would pull the center MOB with Malise and kill it.  I would then move to the mouth of the room.  Med up, sick pet on one of the corner mobs and then repeat for the other corner.  I never had a problem with aggroing another Yeti even when I was fighting next to them.  These guys are indeed related to the skulking brutes near Dalnir.<br>
<br>
There was two interesting things that happened.  First, for some reason, after a couple days, the wandering mobs stopped appearing.  Then last week's patch came and the wanderers came back.  Once again, a few days after the patch, the wanderes were gone again.  Maybe there is a bug where the mobs stop poping if they are not killed in a certain time. I dunno.  Second interesting thing was something that reminded me of the skulking brutes yet again.  One time during the 5 levels, a nasty drolvarg dropped through the ceiling to party with my pet.  I was lucky in that I was about to begin dancing with a yeti so I had time to tango.<br>
<br>
Cave 2<br>
<br>
I only spent one good excursion here.  There are four static spawns on a 20 min timer and two wandering spawns on a 16 min timer.  After I initially cleared the wandering MOBs (once again starting the stopwatch with the death of the first one), I setup at cave mouth and pull singly the four spawns inside the room.<br>
<br>
Overall, the yeti caves were excellent experience and a very quick way to 44 from 39.  I actually wish I came here earlier since levels 35-39 have been the toughest in my leveling.<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
Zorryn Neblin<br>
Level 44 Mage<br>
Divine Symphony<br>
Terris Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzorryn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zorryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#333333>(3/14/01 5:26:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels3943.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   A note on drops</span><hr size=1> Howdy again,<br>
<br>
One thing I forgot to add:<br>
<br>
The mobs drop Essence of Winter which is needed for Barbarian smithing.  Barb smithers in my guild were pleasantly surprised by this since they originally thought the essence of winter only dropped off the ice giants in Everfrost.  Now, my guild is pretty young (I am only the second char over 40) so this might be well known.<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
Zorryn<br>
