<br>
I camped the Tundra Yetis in cave#1 from levels 41 to 45.  At 44 and 45, about 35% of them are green and the level 44 pet tears through them very efficiently.  At 46 I went to the Glacier Yeti cave.  They max hit for about 93 damage.  They can be pulled the same way the Tundra Yetis can, but there is a lot more down time associated with them.  At level 46 I get about 1/2 a blue bubble per kill.  When I get low mana in the Glacier Yeti cave, I usually go outside and have my pet pick on the low blue spawns that wander by while I med up.  <br>
<br>
While I was getting insane xp solo, It became really boring.  I usually partner up with a druid.  It lowers downtime and maintains my sanity.  <br>
<br>
<br>
